Interview Ready Answer

A website works on a client-server architecture where the browser sends an HTTP request to the server. The server processes the request, interacts with the database if needed, and returns a response (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), which the browser renders into a user interface.

  Final Summary

User enters URL
DNS resolves IP
Request goes to server
Server processes + DB fetch
Response sent
Browser renders UI

